        <p>Semrush's published index is larger on paper, but Ahrefs typically wins on <strong>freshness</strong> — the same link shows up in Ahrefs 6–14 days before Semrush in our spot-checks. For active link building, freshness beats raw size.</p>

        <h3>The Ahrefs blog — proof of concept</h3>
        <p>Ahrefs' own blog (ahrefs.com/blog, led by Tim Soulo) generates an estimated <strong>700,000+ organic visits per month</strong> and ranks for some of the most competitive SEO terms on the planet. They practise exactly what they sell. The YouTube channel is equally strong — both are worth following whether you pay for the tool or not.</p>

