        <h2 id="verdict">Is Ahrefs worth it in 2026? Final verdict</h2>
        <p><strong>For SEO professionals and agencies: yes.</strong> The backlink data is the best in the industry. Site Explorer alone justifies $129–$249/mo if link building is part of your strategy. The math works when you bill clients $2K–$10K/mo for SEO.</p>

        <p><strong>For content teams with writers: yes, with a caveat.</strong> Ahrefs gives you keyword targets and the competitive landscape. But you will need a content optimisation tool (Surfer, Clearscope) on top — Ahrefs does not score content against SERP data. Total tooling cost: $250–$370/mo before writers.</p>

        <p><strong>For small business owners: almost always no.</strong> You open Ahrefs. You see your competitor ranks for 500 keywords and you find 30 opportunities. You cannot write 30 articles this month. You cannot write 3. You can barely write 1. The data is accurate. The execution is impossible without a team. You would spend $129/mo watching your competitors win.</p>

